description:
TAX ASSISTANCE 2018: No income guideline. Providing income tax preparation services 2/1-4/14. Prepares both federal and state tax forms; offers E-filing at all locations. VITA Tax Locator, 800-906-9887.

Ray of Hope Baptist Church
3000 Parkside Drive, Baltimore, MD 21214. Call 410-254-3797
Provides assistance from 2/3-3/24. Walk-in Sat, 9AM-12PM. Now closed.

Coppin State University†
2500 West North Avenue, College of Business, Health and Human†Service Building (HHSB),†Room 108, Baltimore, MD 21216. Located off of West North Avenue connecting to the elevator stair tower, near the McDonald Child Development Center (MCDS) and the South Quad. Call 410-951-3444.
Provides assistance from 2/2-4/14. Walk-in Mon, Wed, and†Fri, 12:00PM-4:30PM†& Sat, 10AM-2PM (Closed on university holidays).

Must bring the following:
-- Valid photo ID for self and spouse.
-- A Social Security card for EACH family member.
-- W-2 forms for all jobs worked in the previous year.
-- Child care provider - name, address and tax ID number.
-- All banking account information (a voided check and/or savings deposit slip).
-- A copy of last year's tax return.
-- Any document or information about money received from the IRS, including the advanced Child Tax Credit.
-- All 1099 forms for other income, if any.
-- Any other tax related documents.

description: FOOD PANTRY: Provides non-perishable food items to eligible individuals in Baltimore City and Baltimore County. Individuals are eligible for food twice for Department of Social Services (DSS) and once for 211MD every 30 days. All callers must be able to provide ID and SS card.†Do not need to call before faxing referral. Monday-Friday from 9AM-4PM. Also, offers diapers sizes 1-6 and Similac Advance formula if available. Diapers are provided to families with children up to 18 months old, and formula is provided to families with children up to 12 months old. Diapers and formula may be provided to families with older†children if the child has a documented disability†(call to confirm availability, and individuals must bring birth certificates and social security cards for children; children with a disability, families must provide documentation).†

description:
Designates Cooling Centers in the county. Cooling centers will be open Mon, Aug 27th - Thurs, Aug 30th.†

Cooling Centers
Senior Activity Centers will be available Fri, Jun 29th, and Mon, July 2nd, 8:30AM-4PM
  • Annapolis Senior Activity Center, 119 South Villa Avenue, Annapolis
  • Arnold Senior Activity Center, 44 Church Road, Arnold
  • Brooklyn Park Senior Activity Center, 202 Hammonds Lane, Brooklyn Park
  • O'Malley Senior Activity Center, 1275 Odenton Road, Odenton
  • Pasadena Senior Activity Center, 4103 Mountain Road, Pasadena
  • Pascal Senior Activity Center, 125 Dorsey Road, Glen Burnie
  • South County Senior Activity Center, 27 Stepneys Lane, Edgewater
Public Libraries will be available Fri, Jun 29-Sat, Jun 30, 9AM-5PM and Mon, July 2, 9AM-9PM
  • Annapolis Area Library: 1410 West Street, Annapolis
  • Broadneck Community Library: 1275 Green Holly Drive, Annapolis
  • Brooklyn Park Community Library: 1 East 11th Avenue, Baltimore
  • Crofton Community Library: 1681 Riedel Road, Crofton
  • Deale Community Library: 5940 Deale-Churchton Road, Deale
  • Eastport-Annapolis Neck Community Library: 269 Hillsmere Drive, Annapolis
  • Edgewater Community Library: 25 Stepneys Lane, Edgewater
  • Glen Burnie Library: 1010 Eastway, Glen Burnie
  • Linthicum Community Library: 400 Shipley Road, Linthicum
  • Odenton Library: 1325 Annapolis Road, Odenton
  • Maryland City at Russett Community Library: 3501 Russett Common, Laurel
  • Mountain Road Community Library: 4730 Mountain Road, Pasadena
  • Severna Park Community Library: 45 West McKinsey Rd
  • Severn Community Library Severn Square Shopping Center, 2624 Annapolis Rd
  • Riviera Beach Community Library: 1130 Duvall Highway, Pasadena
County Police will be available Fri, Jun 29-Tues, July 3 at 8AM.
Community Rooms/Cooling Center have water and restrooms. Medical care is not available and pets are not allowed in cooling centers. Accommodations will be made for service animals.
  • Northern District, 939 Hammonds Lane, Baltimore
  • Eastern District, 204 Pasadena Road, Pasadena
  • Western District, 8273 Telegraph Road, Odenton
  • Southern District, 35 Stepneys Lane, Edgewater
Transportation
Transportation is only provided during normal business hours, Mon-Fri, 8:30AM-4PM. Call 410-222-0022.
